1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,020
Evidence Integrity Enforcer, a DFIR agent with 15 read-only MCP tools.

2
00:00:06,020 --> 00:00:11,260
Every evidence file is sealed with a SHA-256 hash before a single tool runs.

3
00:00:11,260 --> 00:00:13,820
This is constraint by architecture, not by prompt.

4
00:00:13,820 --> 00:00:18,299
Claude invokes volatility plugins, registry queries, event log parsers, YARA scans, and

5
00:00:18,299 --> 00:00:19,660
timeline builder.

6
00:00:19,660 --> 00:00:22,139
Every call logged to JSONL with a UUID.

7
00:00:22,139 --> 00:00:24,379
No shell, no write, no delete.

8
00:00:24,379 --> 00:00:26,620
Those functions don't exist in the server.

9
00:00:26,620 --> 00:00:28,660
The attack surface is zero.

10
00:00:28,780 --> 00:00:31,260
Now the DRS confidence gate.

11
00:00:31,260 --> 00:00:33,740
Each finding is scored on two dimensions.

12
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:39,820
Evidence strength, weighted 0.6, plus cross-tool corroboration, weighted 0.4.

13
00:00:39,820 --> 00:00:45,400
Below the 0.75 threshold, the agent self-corrects, seeks a second independent tool to confirm

14
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,139
before committing.

15
00:00:47,139 --> 00:00:51,220
The yellow self-correction lines are the agent catching itself in real-time and going back

16
00:00:51,220 --> 00:00:53,020
for more evidence.

17
00:00:53,020 --> 00:00:54,900
No human in the loop.

18
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:59,299
parse_evtx catches encoded PowerShell in the security log.

19
00:00:59,299 --> 00:01:01,660
Execution policy bypass.

20
00:01:01,660 --> 00:01:06,379
YARA matches certutil -urlcache — the LOLBin download stage.

21
00:01:06,379 --> 00:01:10,139
A Cobalt Strike beacon signature hits at memory offset 5016.

22
00:01:10,139 --> 00:01:16,820
C2 traffic to 185.220.101.34 on port 8443 — the standard Cobalt Strike HTTPS listener.

23
00:01:16,820 --> 00:01:23,699
Process injection via rundll32 — MITRE ATT&CK technique T1055.001.

24
00:01:23,699 --> 00:01:29,220
Eight findings committed, each with an evidence score, a corroboration count, and UUID provenance

25
00:01:29,220 --> 00:01:32,419
linking back to exact tool calls in the audit trail.

26
00:01:32,419 --> 00:01:36,860
generate_report writes the IR markdown — findings, IOCs, recommendations.

27
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:42,379
export_stix produces a STIX 2.1 bundle — indicator, relationship, and report objects, ready to

28
00:01:42,379 --> 00:01:45,820
push into MISP, OpenCTI, or ThreatConnect.

29
00:01:45,820 --> 00:01:49,300
Threat intel in a format any SOC already consumes.

30
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,300
Investigation complete.

31
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,099
Chain of custody intact.

32
00:01:52,099 --> 00:01:57,099
Defender clock: 34 seconds. Adversary breakout time: 7 minutes.

33
00:01:57,099 --> 00:01:59,419
Every finding, forensically defensible.
